und-color: white;"><span style="font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;, Trebuchet, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 18px; text-align: -webkit-auto;">In the developing world, the latest critical information such as current flooding levels, available vaccines, total casualties and location coordinates are rarely available to the most remote and vulnerable people. Due to the lack of information, Â people&#39;s health and safety as well as the economy have been affected. By the time relief workers are made aware of what is going on, things might have already gone worse. Thus making the rescue and recovery process the much more of a struggle.</span></span><br></div></div><a href="http://phnompenhlab.instedd.org/2012/06/from-idea-to-product.html#more">Read more Â»</a><div class="blogger-post-footer"><img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/9209663197707706977-8080864629149614876?l=phnompenhlab.instedd.org' alt='' /></div><div class="feedflare">
