</div>";s:10:"post_title";s:29:"Malaria Day Zero Alert System";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:255:"The Malaria Day Zero Alert System had the first pilot test in Cambodia on August 1. Â We are trying to use this new system instead of relying only on the paper based report because we know it has the potential to make reporting more accurate, faster an...";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:29:"malaria-day-zero-alert-system";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2012-06-29 04:44:59";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2012-06-28 21:44:59";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:71:"http://www.ilabsoutheastasia.org/?guid=f276f8530c2f5fe6b8da1b2603ed3682";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:56;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"4201";s:11:"post_author";s:2:"18";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2011-11-01 23:54:49";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2011-11-02 07:54:49";s:12:"post_content";s:14627:"<div style="text-align: left;" dir="ltr">
<div id="internal-source-marker_0.5625884224540738" style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: 17.45pt;" dir="ltr"><span style="background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><span id="internal-source-marker_0.5625884224540738" style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-size: large;">Overview</span></span></span></span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 36pt;" dir="ltr"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">As<br /> day-3 reporting model has proved to be an effective mechanism for<br /> reporting cases by SMS, and in light of the move towards the elimination<br /> of malaria in Cambodia, it has been decided to scale up the system<br /> day-0 reporting of all Pf cases from VMWs and health facilities. As the<br /> number of cases will be higher for day-0 than day-3 and given the<br /> probable need for more widespread implementation it has been decided to<br /> move to a more robust internet based platform.</span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 36pt;" dir="ltr"><span style="background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><br /></span></span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 36pt;" dir="ltr"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><span style="background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">Malaria Day Zero Alert System is a web base application with SMS service that Â enable the health center staff (</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">HC</span><span style="background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">) and village malaria worker (</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">VMW</span><span style="background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">)<br /> to send malaria case reporting Â from the village or health center via<br /> SMS to the system and make automatic SMS alert to supervised health<br /> center, operational district (OD), Provincial heath department(</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">PHD</span><span style="background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;">),<br /> National Level or System Administrator. Online system also provide<br /> ability to view Â report, manage users and places, set threshold, Â send<br /> alert to group or individual, and templates message setting. The project<br /> is currently being hosted with url </span><span style="background-color: transparent; color: blue; font-weight: bold; text-indent: 23px; vertical-align: baseline;"><a href="http://md0.cnm.gov.org/">http://md0.cnm.gov.org</a></span></span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; text-decoration: none; text-indent: 36pt;" dir="ltr"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; margin-top: 0pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: 36pt;" dir="ltr"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="font-family: 'Trebuchet MS', sans-serif;">The training has been trained to the user in Kampot province users from 1st to 5th of August 2011. All the user get one cell phone and Mobitel SIM card.</span></div>
