e is a free and open-source tool that makes it easy for anyone to create and run projects that interact via voi...";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:25:"verboice-tutorials-part-1";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2013-01-19 05:51:40";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2013-01-18 22:51:40";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:71:"http://www.ilabsoutheastasia.org/?guid=9597ba0b0380d4858ada821212d1435e";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:107;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"6060";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"6";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-01-19 05:51:40";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-01-18 22:51:40";s:12:"post_content";s:3000:"<p>For the last two years <a href="http://ndt.instedd.org/2011/11/verboice-listen-and-respond-to-voice-of.html">we have been working</a> hard on a new tool called <a href="http://verboice.instedd.org/">Verboice</a> to simplify the creation of voice-enabled applications.</p>
<p>Verboice is a free and open-source tool that makes it easy for anyone to create and run projects that interact via voice, allowing your users to listen and record messages in their own language and dialect or answer questions with a phone keypad.</p>
<p>To make it easier to get started, I created a few simple videos.</p>
